11 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
12 Section 1. (a) On and after July 1, 2025, no state agency shall seek or
13 implement:
14 (1) (A) A medicaid state plan, state plan amendment, state
15 demonstration or waiver pursuant to section 1115 or 1915 of the federal
16 social security act that would expand coverage to any additional
17 individuals or class of individuals or would increase any cost to the state
18 unless the legislature expressly consents to, and approves of, such
19 medicaid state plan, state plan amendment, state demonstration or waiver
20 by an act of the legislature.
21 (B) The provisions of this paragraph shall not affect any state plan
22 amendment or waiver program already being implemented prior to July 1,
23 2025; or
24 (2) any changes to funding structures, day services or targeted
25 case management services for persons with intellectual or
26 developmental disabilities unless the legislature expressly consents to
27 and approves of such changes by an act of the legislature.
28 (b) (1) When the legislature is not in session, a state agency may
29 request approval from the legislative coordinating council to authorize
30 a medicaid state plan, state plan amendment, state demonstration or
31 waiver or changes to funding structures, day services or targeted case
32 management services for persons with intellectual or developmental
33 disabilities.
34 (2) Pursuant to K.S.A. 46-1202, and amendments thereto, the
35 legislative coordinating council may approve or refuse an agency's

